external_knowledge:
- 'Troubled test cases' refers to test cases that failed their execution;
- 'QA area' is synonymous with 'QA Environment';
- 'Recently' in this context means within the last 30 days;
- 'Who updated them last' is the user who made the latest modification to the test cases.

sql:
SELECT test_step_id, test_case_id, step_no, step_description, keyword, expected_result, created_by, created_date, last_modified_by, last_modified_date
FROM test_steps
WHERE status = 'pass';

SELECT test_suite_name
FROM test_suites
WHERE test_suite_id = 1;

SELECT users.user_name, users.email, users.role
FROM users
WHERE users.user_id IN (
    SELECT created_by FROM test_suites
    UNION
    SELECT created_by FROM test_cases
)
AND users.user_id NOT IN (
    SELECT executed_by FROM test_case_execution
);

SELECT DISTINCT test_case_id
FROM test_case_execution
WHERE executed_by = 1 AND execution_date = '2023-05-01';

external_knowledge:
- 'test cases' are likened to 'plants' in a garden;
- 'users who executed test cases' are called 'gardeners' who planted these plants;
- 'execution_date' is referred to as 'dates of planting';
- 'ExecutionOrder' suggests the sequence of planting, with the most recent planting being the freshest.

- "primary tester" refers to the user with ID 1;
- "haven't been looked at yet" means these test cases have not been executed by the user with ID 1;
- "project one" corresponds to `project_id = 1`.
